  "intro": "Danilo Goffi (born 3 December 1972 in Legnano) is a former Italian long-distance runner, who specializes in the marathon. He represented his country at the 1996 Summer Olympics and has also competed at the World Championships in Athletics. He was the silver medallist in the marathon at the 1998 European Athletics Championships. He won two times the Italian national championships of the marathon, the first time in 1995 when he was 23 years old, and the second time, 19 years after in 2014 when he was 42."
